sexpression.stream

Class ASEInputStreamReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • sexpression.stream.ASEInputStreamReader

  • public class ASEInputStreamReader
extends java.lang.Object
    The ASEInputStreamReader parses ASExpressions that have been serialized in verbatim form off any input stream.

    • Method Detail

      • read

        public ASExpression read()
                  throws java.io.IOException,
                         InvalidVerbatimStreamException
        Invoke this method to parse one ASExpression off the decorated stream. This method interprets the stream to have ASExpressions in either verbatim or base64/canonical form delineated by nothing. (In other words, s-expressions in the verbatim form should be "back to back" on the stream in order for subsequent calls to read() to give the desired behavior..)
        Returns:
        This method returns the parsed ASExpression.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - This method throws if reading from the decorated stream throws.
        InvalidVerbatimStreamException - This method throws if there is invalid data on the stream. In order for s-expressions to be valid, the must begin either with a digit (denoting a string type) or a paren (denoting a list). If the parser expects one of these two and finds something else, the data is invalid.

      • readASE

        private ASExpression readASE(byte openchar)
                      throws java.io.IOException,
                             InvalidVerbatimStreamException
        This is a private helper method for read(). This method will call either readString(...) or readList() for help, based on if the first character of the next s-expression on the stream is a digit or an open paren. Important: this method expects that this first (and crucial) character has already been read off the stream.
        Parameters:
        openchar - This is the (crucial) character which this method uses to determine if the next s-expression is type list or string.
        Returns:
        This method returns the next s-expression on the list as an ASExpression.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - This method throws if reading from the decorated stream throws.
        InvalidVerbatimStreamException - This method throws if there is invalid data on the stream. In order for s-expressions to be valid, the must begin either with a digit (denoting a string type) or a paren (denoting a list). If the parser expects one of these two and finds something else, the data is invalid.

                               throws java.io.IOException,

      • readString

        private ASExpression readString(byte openchar)
                         throws java.io.IOException
        This is a private helper method for readASE(). This method reads one byte string off the stream and constructs a new StringExpression which represents it. Important: This method assumes that the length and the colon have already been read off the stream!
        Parameters:
        len - This method will read this number of bytes off the stream to construct the StringExpression
        Returns:
        This method returns the constructed StringExpression which represents the string read off the stream.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - This method throws if there was a problem reading the proper number of bytes off the stream (basically, EOF).

      • readList

        private ListExpression readList()
                         throws java.io.IOException,
                                InvalidVerbatimStreamException
        This is a private helper method for readASE(). This method parses a list s-expression off the stream and constructs a new SExpressionlist which represents it. Important: This method assumes that the open paren for the list has already been read off the stream!
        Returns:
        This method returns the new SExpressionList which represents what was parsed off the stream.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - This method throws if there was a problem reading the proper number of bytes off the stream.
